X\in M_2(\mathbb{R})
\det(\exp X)=e^{\mathrm{Tr}\, X}
X
X=PJP^{-1}
J
\exp (PJP^{-1})=P(\exp J)P^{-1}
\det P(\exp J)P^{-1}=\det \exp J
J=\begin{pmatrix} a & 0 \\ 0 & b \end{pmatrix}
a=b
\det \exp J=e^{a+b}=e^{\mathrm{Tr}\, J}=e^{\mathrm{Tr}\, X}
X
J
J=\begin{pmatrix} a & 1 \\ 0 & a \end{pmatrix}
\exp J=\exp\begin{pmatrix} a & 0 \\ 0 & a \end{pmatrix} \exp \begin{pmatrix} 0 & 1 \\ 0 & 0 \end{pmatrix}=\begin{pmatrix} e^a & e^{a+1} \\ e^a & e^{a} \end{pmatrix}
\det \exp J=e^{2a}(1-e)
\exp J
\exp J = \exp \begin{pmatrix} a & 0 \\ 0 & a \end{pmatrix} \exp \begin{pmatrix} 0 & 1 \\ 0 & 0 \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} e^a & 0 \\ 0 & e^a \end{pmatrix} \begin{pmatrix} 1 & 1 \\ 0 & 1 \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} e^a & e^a\\ 0 & e^a \end{pmatrix}
 \exp\begin{pmatrix}0&1\\0&0\end{pmatrix}=I+\begin{pmatrix}0&1\\0&0\end{pmatrix}+\frac1{2!}\begin{pmatrix}0&1\\0&0\end{pmatrix}^2+\ldots =I+\begin{pmatrix}0&1\\0&0\end{pmatrix}=\begin{pmatrix}1&1\\0&1\end{pmatrix}. 
